Lesson 

---------- [L1]


Video link: https://youtu.be/qOatQy1bnLI
Audio link: https://rss.com/podcasts/footnerdprogram/560924/

Creators: Emily Gooding, Katie Lund

Framework:
- definition of pain
- pain as a protective signal and not our enemy
- opioids and chronic pain crisis
- strategic approaches to pain 
- addressing pain with a 6 pillar health approach
- listening closely to our bodies and their signals
- accepting responsibility for our health 
- empowerment to address the pain we experience



Audio lesson notes:
- detailed notes and timestamps from the audio lesson


Experiments (nano to macro)
- Answer this question in your health log: Do you believe pain has an emotional component? Where in your body do you experience pain?
Write about how you deal with pain in your body? Are you happy with the results? What do you believe about pain and how it works 
in our bodies?
- Be open minded to explore new techniques to deal with pain: https://www.thetappingsolution.com/tapping-101/
- If you or a someone you know deals with chronic pain (defined as pain lasting longer than 3 months without a reason)
try this: https://youtu.be/ASKiDfOn6hs
- Reflect on your sleep routine and note any blindspots in your health log
